'''USS ''Fentress'' (AK-180/T-AK-180)''' was an {{sclass-|Alamosa|cargo ship}} acquired by the [[US Navy]] during the final months of World War II. In 1950, she was reactivated and placed into service with the [[Military Sea Transportation Service]] as USNS ''Fentress''. She was ultimately transferred to the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]] and the [[Republic of the Marshall Islands]].
==Construction== ''Fentress'' was launched on 10 March 1945 by [[Kaiser Shipyards|Kaiser Cargo, Inc.]], [[Richmond, California]], under a [[Maritime Commission]] contract, MC hull 2376; sponsored by Mrs. G. M. Ellis; and commissioned 4 May 1945, [[Lieutenant (navy)|Lieutenant]] G. T. Malley, [[USNR]], in command.{{sfn|DANFS|2014}}
==Service history== ===World War II-related service=== After [[sea trial|shakedown]] and availability, ''Fentress'' engaged in local operations until 27 June 1945 when she departed [[San Francisco, California]], to transport cargo among the [[Philippine Islands]]. On 20 February 1946 she was placed out of commission and returned to the [[U.S. Maritime Commission]].{{sfn|DANFS|2014}}
==Service with the MSTS== After the organization of the [[Military Sea Transportation Service]] (MSTS), ''Fentress'' was reacquired on 1 July 1950 for service.{{sfn|DANFS|2014}}
==Merchant service== ''Fentress'' was struck from the [[Naval Vessel Register|Navy List]] on 15 October 1973 and transferred to the Government of the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]] on 20 July 1974.{{sfn|Navsource|2014}}
On 4 July 1982, she was transferred permanently to the [[Republic of the Marshall Islands]], her fate is unknown.{{sfn|Navsource|2014}}
This ship was apparently still docked on the Hawaiian Islands in 1982, as it was seen on the ''[[Magnum P.I.]]'' episode, "I do".{{CN|date=November 2016}}
